# Bordmap reverse proxy for the Coolify deploy (FEN-437, owned by DevOps).
#
# Bordmap ships as a SINGLE image (app on :3000 + self-hosted Convex on :3210,
# see ../../Dockerfile). The browser needs BOTH origins on ONE public domain, so
# this tiny Caddy sits in front of the bordmap container and path-routes:
#
#   /convex*   -> Convex CLOUD origin (:3210)  — the Convex client API/sync.
#                 VITE_CONVEX_URL = https://<host>/convex ; handle_path strips the
#                 /convex prefix so the backend (served at root) sees bare paths.
#                 The token-free smoke hits https://<host>/convex/version -> /version.
#   everything -> the Start (Nitro) app (:3000) — the SPA + its server routes.
#                 No prefix to strip.
#
# Why baked, not bind-mounted: a host bind-mount of a single file fails on
# Coolify (the host source is auto-created as a DIRECTORY -> "mount a directory
# onto a file", OCI bug — inherited LivePlace gotcha FEN-80/FEN-96). The
# Dockerfile.proxy bakes THIS file into the image, reproducible on any host.
#
# SITE_ADDRESS drives scheme/port. Default ':80' = plain HTTP on :80, accepting
# all hostnames — the reliable mode behind Coolify's edge Traefik, which
# terminates TLS and routes the public domain to this container's internal :80
# (so we `expose` :80, never host-publish — host-publishing breaks Coolify's
# domain routing and 404s the public URL, FEN-92).
{$SITE_ADDRESS::80} {
	encode gzip zstd

	# Convex client API/sync (+ the smoke's /version). Strip the /convex prefix.
	handle_path /convex/* {
		reverse_proxy convex-backend:3210
	}

	# Everything else -> the Start app (SPA + server routes). lb_try_* bridges the
	# brief single-replica restart window during Coolify's non-zero-downtime
	# container recreation (a sub-window blip would otherwise 503). GET-only
	# fallback, so a retried dial has no side-effect risk.
	reverse_proxy app:3000 {
		lb_try_duration 3s
		lb_try_interval 250ms
	}
}
